title: IAA Tonight | Aaron Judge Sets American League All-Time Single-Season Home Run Record
description: Aaron Judge is the American League’s all-time single-season home run king. The New York Yankees superstar surpassed Roger Maris's record with his 62nd homer of 2022 during our show! LeSean McCoy, Leger Douzable and Adam Pacman Jones discuss the historic run by the Yankees slugger as it happened on air.
author: smanderville@houseofathlete.com (Leger Douzable, LeSean Mccoy, Adam Pacman Jones)
